---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About - Korean Saju Guide"
  description="Learn about our mission to share the wisdom of Korean Four Pillars (Saju) with the world through cultural education and ethical practice."
>
  <section class="py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-dark-50 mb-6">
          About <span class="gradient-text">Saju Guide</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-dark-400">
          Bridging ancient Korean wisdom with modern understanding
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-primary-400 mt-8 mb-4">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="text-dark-300">
          Korean Saju Guide was created by a dedicated team of cultural researchers, developers, and writers with a simple yet profound mission: <strong>to demystify the fascinating cultural tradition of Saju (사주) for an English-speaking audience, while maintaining strict historical and philosophical accuracy.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-dark-300 mt-4">
          For too long, Eastern esoteric traditions have been either sensationalized as magical fortune-telling or oversimplified into generic daily horoscopes. We believe that Saju—the ancient system of Four Pillars—deserves to be explored, appreciated, and respected as a highly sophisticated, centuries-old framework for psychological profiling and self-reflection.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-accent-400 mt-12 mb-4">Our Editorial Standards & Expertise</h2>
        <p class="text-dark-300">
          Trust and accuracy (E-E-A-T) are the cornerstones of our platform. Our content is not AI-generated fluff or hastily translated material from unreliable sources. 
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-dark-300 space-y-2 mt-4">
          <li><strong>Rigorous Research:</strong> Our guides are based on traditional texts and established conventions of the Sexagenary cycle, Yin-Yang theory, and Five Elements philosophy.</li>
          <li><strong>Algorithmic Precision:</strong> The algorithms powering our Saju Calculator and Compatibility Tool were built from the ground up to accurately calculate the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches based on the traditional lunisolar calendar conversions, adjusting accurately for timezones.</li>
          <li><strong>Psychological Empathy:</strong> We strictly avoid fear-mongering. We do not believe in "cursed" charts or fatalistic predictions. Every article is written with the goal of fostering self-acceptance and empathy.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-primary-400 mt-12 mb-4">What We Offer</h2>
        <p class="text-dark-300 mt-4">
          Our platform provides free, accessible educational resources and interactive tools to help you explore your cosmic blueprint:
        </p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6 not-prose">
          <div class="p-6 bg-dark-800/40 rounded-xl border border-dark-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold text-dark-100 mb-2">Interactive Tools</h3>
            <p class="text-dark-400 text-sm">Calculate your personal Four Pillars chart or check relationship dynamics with our complex, client-side calculators.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-dark-800/40 rounded-xl border border-dark-700">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold text-dark-100 mb-2">In-Depth Guides</h3>
            <p class="text-dark-400 text-sm">Explore deep, analytical articles explaining the mechanics of the Heavenly Stems, Earthly Branches, and the cultural context of Saju in modern Korea.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-accent-400 mt-12 mb-4">Our Commitment to Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-dark-300">
          We understand that birth data is sensitive information. That is why <strong>Korean Saju Guide operates entirely on the client-side.</strong> When you enter your birth date and time into our calculators, the processing happens directly within your own web browser. We have no databases, we do not store your information, and we certainly do not sell it. Your privacy is absolute.
        </p>

        <h2>Important Disclaimer</h2>
        <div class="bg-dark-800/50 border border-dark-700 rounded-xl p-6 not-prose">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-yellow-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-dark-50 mb-2">For Entertainment & Self-Reflection Only</h4>
              <p class="text-dark-400 text-sm">
                The content and tools on this website are provided for entertainment, cultural education, and personal reflection purposes only. They are not intended to provide professional advice of any kind—medical, legal, financial, psychological, or otherwise. Saju readings should not be used as the basis for important life decisions. We encourage you to enjoy exploring this cultural tradition while maintaining a healthy perspective on its role in modern life.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          Have questions, suggestions, or feedback? We'd love to hear from you. Visit our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a> to get in touch.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
